- To add Cardinal Components API to a 1.19.2 project, insert the following lines into your "build.gradle" and "gradle.properties" files.

- Insert this into "build.gradle" under "repositories":

maven {
        name = "Ladysnake Mods"
        url = 'https://maven.ladysnake.org/releases'
    }

- Insert this into "build.gradle" under "dependencies":

modImplementation "dev.onyxstudios.cardinal-components-api:cardinal-components-base:${project.cca_version}"
 include "dev.onyxstudios.cardinal-components-api:cardinal-components-base:${project.cca_version}"

- Note, this also applies to "cardinal-component-entity" and "cardinal-components-world"

- Insert this into "gradle.properties" under your "dependencies" section :

  cca_version=5.0.2

- To apply changes, simply re-sync your gradle project.
